race.comment: WAILEA (14) jumped out well and was only beaten 1.7L over 1200m at Mornington on debut. Draws an inside barrier and is open to plenty of improvement. Should go close. Ditto BRUTAL WORLD (4), who is third-up and ready to show his best form. That would be good enough, but she needs a good ride pushing over from a wide gate. Wary of GOOD HARMONY (12) on debut. Well-bred and her latest jumpout was sharp. Has the blinkers on and elevate her if the big money comes. REGOR (11) is in a leading metro yard and found a place at Swan Hill off a longish spell. Has a soft draw and the winkers on and fitter is likely to race well. BORN SURVIVOR (1) is third up with more to give and raced favourite at Echuca last time.
